63580](https://github.com/entireio/cli/actions/runs/22831463580) (commit `a258927d`) shows 2/42 cursor-cli tests failing: `TestPartialStaging` and `TestUserSplitsAgentChanges`. Additionally, the current branch HEAD (`e90e3f9c`) reverted the per-session config isolation fix, meaning the ENOENT race condition is also unfixed.\\n     6→\\n     7→There are **two independent flakiness sources** for cursor-cli:\\n     8→\\n     9→---\\n    10→\\n    11→## Finding 1: Premature WaitFor Settle (Root Cause of CI Failures)\\n    12→\\n    13→### Evidence\\n    14→\\n    15→**TestPartialStaging** — second prompt produced no file changes:\\n    16→- `split_commits_test.go:89`: `git commit -m Add goodbye world failed: exit status 1` — \\\"nothing added to commit\\\"\\n    17→- Console shows agent started, displayed \\\"Claude 4.6 Opus (Thinking)\\\" + status bar `/ commands · @ files · ! shell`, but never produced output\\n    18→- `RunPrompt` returned **without error** (no timeout), meaning WaitFor matched and settled\\n    19→\\n    20→**TestUserSplitsAgentChanges** — agent created zero files:\\n    21→- `split_commits_test.go:27-28`: `expected files matching docs/c.md` / `docs/d.md` — empty\\n    22→- Same pattern: agent showed \\\"Thinking\\\" + `/ commands` status bar, then WaitFor settled\\n    23→\\n    24→### Root Cause\\n    25→\\n    26→The Cursor CLI's TUI **always shows `/ commands` in the status bar**, including during the \\\"Thinking\\\" phase. The WaitFor mechanism:\\n    27→\\n    28→1. Matches `/ commands` pattern against full pane content (line 138 of tmux.go)\\n    29→2. Checks content changed since Send (it did — prompt was echoed)\\n    30→3. Waits for 2 seconds of stable content (`settleTime = 2 * time.Second`)\\n    31→4. Returns success\\n    32→\\n    33→**The problem**: When the model takes >2 seconds to start producing visible output after \\\"Thinking\\\" starts, the pane content is stable (nothing is changing visually), and WaitFor settles on the stale `/ commands` text. The test thinks the agent finished, but it's still thinking.\\n    34→\\n    35→This explains why 40/42 tests pass — most of the time the model responds fast enough that the content keeps changing (file edits, response text), preventing premature settle.\\n    36→\\n    37→### Fix: Use Completion-Specific Pattern\\n    38→\\n    39→**File**: `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`\\n    40→\\n    41→Change the completion WaitFor in `RunPrompt` (line 113) from:\\n    42→```go\\n    43→content, waitErr := s.WaitFor(a.PromptPattern(), timeout)\\n    44→```\\n    45→to:\\n    46→```go\\n    47→content, waitErr := s.WaitFor(`Add a follow-up`, timeout)\\n    48→```\\n    49→\\n    50→The `Add a follow-up` text only appears in Cursor's input box **after** the agent finishes processing a prompt. It does NOT appear during the \\\"Thinking\\\" phase.\\n    51→\\n    52→Keep `PromptPattern()` as `/ commands` for initial startup detection (used in `acceptTrustDialogIfNeeded` and the startup WaitFor).\\n    53→\\n    54→Similarly update `StartSession`'s `SendPrompt` flow if it exists, and the `Session` `WaitForReady` pattern.\\n    55→\\n    56→---\\n    57→\\n    58→## Finding 2: ENOENT Config Race (Reverted Fix)\\n    59→\\n    60→### Evidence\\n    61→\\n    62→The current HEAD (`e90e3f9c`) reverted commit `a258927d` which isolated each cursor session's config directory. Without isolation, parallel cursor sessions write to the shared `~/.config/cursor/cli-config.json` via atomic temp-file rename, causing ENOENT crashes.\\n    63→\\n    64→### Fix: Re-apply Config Isolation\\n    65→\\n    66→**File**: `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`\\n    67→\\n    68→Re-implement `cursorConfigDir()` from commit `a258927d`:\\n    69→- Create unique temp dir per session: `/tmp/cursor-e2e-config-<random>/`\\n    70→- Set `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` and `HOME` to this directory\\n    71→- Pre-seed `cursor/cli-config.json` with `{}`\\n    72→- Register cleanup via `s.OnClose()`\\n    73→\\n    74→---\\n    75→\\n    76→## Files to Modify\\n    77→\\n    78→| File | Change |\\n    79→|------|--------|\\n    80→| `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go` | Change completion WaitFor pattern to `Add a follow-up`; re-add `cursorConfigDir()` per-session isolation |\\n    81→\\n    82→## Verification\\n    83→\\n    84→1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n    85→2. `mise run test:e2e:canary` — Vogon canary must pass\\n    86→3. `mise run test:e2e --agent cursor-cli` — full cursor-cli suite (requires user approval due to API costs)\\n    87→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"8222b9e2-e611-4488-abb4-95169786e0dc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T05:28:20.801Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/.claude/plans/inherited-exploring-treehouse.md\",\"content\":\"# Deep Dive: Why Cursor CLI E2E Tests Are Flaky\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCI run [22831463580](https://github.com/entireio/cli/actions/runs/22831463580) (commit `a258927d`) shows 2/42 cursor-cli tests failing: `TestPartialStaging` and `TestUserSplitsAgentChanges`. Additionally, the current branch HEAD (`e90e3f9c`) reverted the per-session config isolation fix, meaning the ENOENT race condition is also unfixed.\\n\\nThere are **two independent flakiness sources** for cursor-cli:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Finding 1: Premature WaitFor Settle (Root Cause of CI Failures)\\n\\n### Evidence\\n\\n**TestPartialStaging** — second prompt produced no file changes:\\n- `split_commits_test.go:89`: `git commit -m Add goodbye world failed: exit status 1` — \\\"nothing added to commit\\\"\\n- Console shows agent started, displayed \\\"Claude 4.6 Opus (Thinking)\\\" + status bar `/ commands · @ files · ! shell`, but never produced output\\n- `RunPrompt` returned **without error** (no timeout), meaning WaitFor matched and settled\\n\\n**TestUserSplitsAgentChanges** — agent created zero files:\\n- `split_commits_test.go:27-28`: `expected files matching docs/c.md` / `docs/d.md` — empty\\n- Same pattern: agent showed \\\"Thinking\\\" + `/ commands` status bar, then WaitFor settled\\n\\n### Root Cause\\n\\nThe Cursor CLI's TUI **always shows `/ commands` in the status bar**, including during the \\\"Thinking\\\" phase. The WaitFor mechanism:\\n\\n1. Matches `/ commands` pattern against full pane content (line 138 of tmux.go)\\n2. Checks content changed since Send (it did — prompt was echoed)\\n3. Waits for 2 seconds of stable content (`settleTime = 2 * time.Second`)\\n4. Returns success\\n\\n**The problem**: When the model takes >2 seconds to start producing visible output after \\\"Thinking\\\" starts, the pane content is stable (nothing is changing visually), and WaitFor settles on the stale `/ commands` text. The test thinks the agent finished, but it's still thinking.\\n\\nThis explains why 40/42 tests pass — most of the time the model responds fast enough that the content keeps changing (file edits, response text), preventing premature settle.\\n\\n### Fix: Use Completion-Specific Pattern\\n\\n**File**: `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`\\n\\nChange the completion WaitFor in `RunPrompt` (line 113) from:\\n```go\\ncontent, waitErr := s.WaitFor(a.PromptPattern(), timeout)\\n```\\nto:\\n```go\\ncontent, waitErr := s.WaitFor(`Add a follow-up`, timeout)\\n```\\n\\nThe `Add a follow-up` text only appears in Cursor's input box **after** the agent finishes processing a prompt. It does NOT appear during the \\\"Thinking\\\" phase.\\n\\nKeep `PromptPattern()` as `/ commands` for initial startup detection (used in `acceptTrustDialogIfNeeded` and the startup WaitFor).\\n\\nSimilarly update `StartSession`'s `SendPrompt` flow if it exists, and the `Session` `WaitForReady` pattern.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Finding 2: ENOENT Config Race (Reverted Fix)\\n\\n### Evidence\\n\\nThe current HEAD (`e90e3f9c`) reverted commit `a258927d` which isolated each cursor session's config directory. Without isolation, parallel cursor sessions write to the shared `~/.config/cursor/cli-config.json` via atomic temp-file rename, causing ENOENT crashes.\\n\\n### Fix: Re-apply Config Isolation\\n\\n**File**: `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`\\n\\nRe-implement `cursorConfigDir()` from commit `a258927d`:\\n- Create unique temp dir per session: `/tmp/cursor-e2e-config-<random>/`\\n- Set `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` and `HOME` to this directory\\n- Pre-seed `cursor/cli-config.json` with `{}`\\n- Register cleanup via `s.OnClose()`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go` | Change completion WaitFor pattern to `Add a follow-up`; re-add `cursorConfigDir()` per-session isolation |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n2. `mise run test:e2e:canary` — Vogon canary must pass\\n3. `mise run test:e2e --agent cursor-cli` — full cursor-cli suite (requires user approval due to API costs)\\n\",\"numLines\":87,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":87}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"0a8edad6-0510-47e3-a3a9-2f492249c20e\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8222b9e2-e611-4488-abb4-95169786e0dc\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"599952a0-b4b6-41ff-9176-7b268429c876\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"inherited-exploring-treehouse\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_012Mb9kmUhakzs8h4arrVs99\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_019HrNhkFaWZkg6axxZEbA23\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e/implement.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":48593,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":14549,\"output_tokens\":143,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":48593,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYrxHT4Gg7zGcxD8TRx81\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"c6206dab-ea50-43d6-bb3e-d59834b0aecb\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T05:28:20.817Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c6206dab-ea50-43d6-bb3e-d59834b0aecb\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"599952a0-b4b6-41ff-9176-7b268429c876\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"inherited-exploring-treehouse\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_019HrNhkFaWZkg6axxZEbA23\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_019HrNhkFaWZkg6axxZEbA23\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T05:28:20.825Z\",\"uuid\":\"ec015eba-2dd9-4b93-9b90-53ace2646268\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c6206dab-ea50-43d6-bb3e-d59834b0aecb\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"599952a0-b4b6-41ff-9176-7b268429c876\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"inherited-exploring-treehouse\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_019HrNhkFaWZkg6axxZEbA23\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# E2E Implement Fixes\\n     2→\\n     3→Apply fixes for E2E test failures, verify with scoped E2E tests.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Inputs\\n     6→\\n     7→This procedure accepts findings from one of:\\n     8→- **`/e2e:triage-ci` output** -- findings report already in conversation context\\n     9→- **`/e2e:debug` output** -- root cause analysis already in conversation context\\n    10→- **Standalone description** -- user describes known failure and desired fix\\n    11→\\n    12→## Step 1: Identify Fixes\\n    13→\\n    14→From the findings in context, identify actionable fixes:\\n    15→\\n    16→### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n    17→\\n    18→For agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n    19→\\n    20→```\\n    21→**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n    22→  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n    23→  - Change: <what will be modified -- e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n    24→```\\n    25→\\n    26→Common flaky fixes:\\n    27→- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n    28→- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n    29→- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n    30→- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n    31→- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n    32→- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n    33→- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n    34→- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n    35→\\n    36→### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\\n    37→\\n    38→```\\n    39→**Root cause analysis:**\\n    40→  - Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n    41→  - Suspected location: <file:function>\\n    42→  - Description: <what's wrong and why>\\n    43→  - Proposed fix: <what code change would address it>\\n    44→```\\n    45→\\n    46→## Step 2: Ask the User\\n    47→\\n    48→Prompt the user:\\n    49→\\n    50→> **Should I fix these?**\\n    51→> - [list of tests with classifications and proposed fixes]\\n    52→> - You can select all, specific tests, or skip.\\n    53→\\n    54→Wait for user response before proceeding.\\n    55→\\n    56→## Step 3: Apply Fixes\\n    57→\\n    58→For **flaky** fixes the user approved:\\n    59→1. Apply fixes directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n    60→2. Run static checks:\\n    61→   ```bash\\n    62→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n    63→   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n    64→   ```\\n    65→3. **Run real E2E tests to verify the fix.** Scope depends on what was changed:\\n    66→   - **Agent-specific fix** (e.g., `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`, one agent's config/trust/env): run the full suite for that agent only:\\n    67→     ```bash\\n    68→     mise run test:e2e --agent <agent>\\n    69→     ```\\n    70→   - **Shared test infra fix** (e.g., `e2e/agents/agent.go`, `e2e/testutil/`, `TmuxSession`, test helpers): run the full suite for all agents that failed, since the fix could affect any of them:\\n    71→     ```bash\\n    72→     mise run test:e2e --agent <agent1>\\n    73→     mise run test:e2e --agent <agent2>\\n    74→     # ... for each agent that had failures\\n    75→     ```\\n    76→   - **Test prompt fix** (e.g., changed wording in a specific test): run that test across all agents that failed it:\\n    77→     ```bash\\n    78→     mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n    79→     ```\\n    80→   This step is mandatory -- canary tests use the Vogon fake agent and cannot verify agent-specific behavior (trust dialogs, env propagation, config directories, etc.).\\n    81→4. If any step fails, investigate and adjust. Report what happened to the user.\\n    82→\\n    83→For **real-bug** fixes the user approved:\\n    84→1. Apply the fix directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n    85→2. Run static checks and unit tests:\\n    86→   ```bash\\n    87→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n    88→   mise run test        # Unit tests\\n    89→   mise run test:e2e:canary  # Canary tests\\n    90→   ```\\n    91→3. **Run real E2E tests to verify the fix.** Same scoping rules as flaky fixes above:\\n    92→   - **Agent-specific change** -> full suite for that agent\\n    93→   - **Shared CLI/infra change** -> full